# MillOS — local environment configuration
# Copy this file to `.env.local` for local development. `.env.local` is gitignored.
#
# IMPORTANT: There is NO build-time Gemini API key.
# The Gemini API key is entered at runtime in the in-app AI / Gemini settings modal
# and stored only in your browser's localStorage (key: "millos-ai-config").
# It is never embedded in the client bundle — see the commented `define` in vite.config.ts.
# The data you send to Gemini goes directly from your browser to Google.

# Enable the service worker during local development.
# (Production builds register it automatically; leave unset for normal `npm run dev`.)
# VITE_ENABLE_SW=true
